english:
  title: A Letter to My Nephew Yeon-Chung
  author: Lee Hoon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your father, though he departed this world early,
    Your uncle, fortunately, still remains.
    What difference could love and care make?
    Do not measure kinship by blood alone.

    Strive for advancement and renown,
    Guard the family gate with sincerity and trust.
    My only hope is that you perfect loyalty and filial piety,
    So your noble name may light the way for all who come after.
  footnotes:
    - 立揚 (ipyang/rising and flourishing) and 顯達 (hyeondal/prominence and achievement) together express the classical Confucian ideal of social advancement through virtue.
    - The final couplet emphasizes the Confucian virtues of 忠孝 (loyalty and filial piety), which were considered the foundation of both personal character and family honor in East Asian culture.
